To calculate the LIX readability score, I will follow the steps described by its creator, Carl-Hugo Sundgren, in the 1960s. LIX is an index that estimates the readability of a text based on the number of letters per word and the number of words per sentence. The LIX score is calculated using the following formula:

LIX = (antal ord/antal meningar) + (antal bokstäver/antalet ord) * 100 / längden på meningarna

However, this formula is for long texts and adjusted LIX score is suitable here, since the text is not very long. 

 Adjusted LIX = ((antal bokstäver/antal ord) + 2*(antal ord/antal meningar))

 So I used this formula. 

1. First, count the number of words in the text: 
 Det (1), är (2), detta (3), tillstånd (4), som (5), man (6), kallar (7), för (8), aids (9), Så (10), vitt (11), man (12), vet (13), så (14), leder (15), en (16), obehandlad (17), hiv-infektion (18), förr (19), eller (20), senare (21), till (22), döden (23) Det (24), finns (25), en (26), storts (27), medicin (28), som (29), bromsar (30), sjukdomsförloppet (31), den (32), heter (33), bromsmedicin (34), Den (35), medicinen (36), kan (37), hålla (38), virushalten (39), i (40), blodet (41), på (42), en (43), så (44), låg (45), nivå (46), så (47), att (48), immunförsvaret (49), inte (50), slås (51), ut (52), och (53), den (54), smittade (55), inte (56), utvecklar (57), aids (58), Smittsamheten (59), vid (60), en (61), effektiv (62), behandling (63), minskar (64).

 There are 64 words.

2. Next, count the number of sentences: 
Det finns fem meningar, but one is relatively short we may reduce this number for accuracy.

Average sentence length in characters of the 4 other sentences adds up to roughly:  82.5, 71.5 ,87, and 47, the last we won't have taken, for overall longer sentences an average then of (82.5 + 71.5 + 87 )/3 is (76.3+87)/2 is 81.6. Therefore I'm using this. 

Number of sentences 5. (Using shorter or longer may also used.)

3. Count the number of letters in the text: 
 Det = 3, är = 2, detta = 5,  ...  We'll add the total number.
3 + 2 + 5 + 8 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 4 + 3 + 5 + 4 + 10 + 2 + 4 + 3 + 21 + 7 + 5 + 4 + 8 + 13 + 5 + 7 + 4 + 22 + 4+ 7 + 3 + 4 + 12 + 9 + 5 + 2 + 8 + 3 + 7 + 12 + 7 + 10 + 3 + 3 + 10 + 21 + 14 + 3 + 4 + 7 + 3 + 15 + 4 + 8 + 5 + 17 + 10 + 4 + 3 + 4 + 20 + 3 + 3 + 8 + 8 + 7 + 5 + 6 + 4 + 9 + 4 = 329.


 Then you calculate the LIX score using the formula:
 
1. Average number of letters per word = 329 letters / 64 words = 5.14
2. Average number of words per sentence = 64 words / 5 sentences = 12.8
3. Calculate the Adjusted LIX score = (antal bokstäver/antal ord) + 2*(antal ord/antal meningar).  
   = 5.14 + 2*12.8 = 30.74 

Adjusted LIX = 30.74